data.text: The Houston Rockets were founded in 1967. The team played in San Diego for four years before relocating to Houston. The Rockets became part of the NBA in 1969 and won 15 games their first season. The Rockets play in the NBAâ€™s Southwest Division along with the Dallas Mavericks, Memphis Grizzlies, New Orleans Hornets and San Antonio Spurs. Among their most famous players include Calvin Murphy, Clyde Drexler, Elvin Hayes, Hakeem Olajuwon, Kenny Smith, Moses Malone, Ralph Sampson, Robert Horry, Rodney McCray, Rudy Tomjanovich, Shane Battier, Steve Francis, Tracy McGrady and Yao Ming.
